@node "INTRO" "Introduction"
  Nice name, what does it do? WangiPad (from now on WP) is a launch pad
utility, it lets you run programs easily without opening 101 drawers to get to
them. 
  WP is different from the vast majority of launch pad utilities, it brings up
a window containing a list of programs on your screen (lets call it a pad).
Thereas most add items to the Workbench tools menu or create ranks or docks of
buttons. The advantages of WP method is that you can get a lot more choices in
a lot less space. Disadvantages... none of course.
@endnode

@node "FEATURES" "Features"
  Why use WangiPad?
  
  1. It uses list representation rather than buttons or menuitems, thus 
     saving space.
     
  2. It supports droping icons on items, passing them as arguments to the
     command.
     
  3. Each item in the list can launch a command or an ARexx command/script,
     or both.
     
  4. The pad uses a user defined font, position, dimensions, titles and 
     screen.
  
  5. You can use a hotkey to show/hide the pad.
  
  6. It has a separate preference editor, thus reducing the memory 
     requirements of the main program.

  7. It can launch programs as if you had double clicked them from
     Workbench.
@endnode

